@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                             @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


   * What is Stereo Crypter ?

     Stereo Crypter is a program made to crypt and hide your datas in old
     stereograms pictures.

   * But, what is a stereogram ?

     A stereogram is a picture hidden in another picture. You must squint
     to see the hidden picture. But, this is only the theory. In the facts,
     it's very hard to see these pictures. So why not to hide datas instead
     of a picture. That's the idea of Stereo Crypter.

   * Overview of Stereo Crypter.

     Stereo Crypter was made in AMOS Pro v2.0. So, that's why it's not a
     wonderful workbench program with buttons, checkmarks, sliders ...
     The interface is graphically very poor (inspirated by MS-DOS, you
     see?!?)
     It is composed by a menu in text mode + a stereogram view when
     crypting/decrypting.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

                             @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}


   It's very easy to install Stereo Crypter, just follow these steps:

   - Copy your directory Libs/ to your LIBS:

     (There is just the Iff.library)
     
     If you have already installed this library, you could pass to the next
     step.
     Just be sure you have the latest version of this library.

   - Make a new directory for Stereo Crypter.

   - Copy the documentation "Stereo Crypter.guide" and 
     "Stereo Crypter.guide.info" to the new directory.

   - Copy the program "Stereo Crypter" and "Stereo Crypter.info" to the new
     directory.
@endnode

